y, our dedicated test doesn’t use reflection, except for ClassLoader. I’m also considering the implications of ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader in Native Image contexts and uncertainties around null returns. It's a lot to unpack!\\n\\n**Exploring class loading issues**\\n\\nI'm considering the implications of having a null situation where there’s no loadClass line, which would mean only using Class.forName. To ensure a non-null environment, I might need to create a URLClassLoader. But then there's the concern about Native Image and its restrictions on dynamic class loading. It seems defining or loading new classes is unsupported. I’m thinking about crafting a ClassLoader subclass that delegates calls to loadClass, but I wonder if this could violate the dynamic loading pattern by preventing new class definitions. It’s intricate!\\n\\n**Considering Java imports**\\n\\nI’m looking into Java imports and noticed we inserted CoreVersionUtil after ConsoleAppender but maybe it needs to be before core.joran to maintain the alphabetical order. The imports so far are ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender, ch.qos.logback.core.joran..., and ch.qos.logback.core.util..., which might be affected by case sensitivity. I think checking the import ordering in other files could really help clarify things and ensure everything is consistent.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0d09c83708f59684016a0573cd8c3081928b7ed1194e188354\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqBXPgEHyzSghmnOO-yjWN7lpj6p_KZECxmeYsLYVHKcAgP8R6tdkDfNwOrS7bjyMQxBL26zgdg6KtERo7Su2wq3upV0kGLNPILYsFXbJeGMU4Cur6CHSigOmVj9d7EUgaZVGKbiryWOLW0eiydKOSJ_0vQJxVLo2KPVOj5suRDV_1Xw-w_WSg9jTI4MquMb9_oZPDqhGcrIGQp8YotqETT40CbbMrjWxmcxHXKdTvtP4LFUxYCSvTC1SLSuo0Hhfw2PYZ5LkbZhWRnjXZAgnfc5weSWjpeOqOcIXh-HSJ4Xysc-BTUkVjMq8QBfFYfB-elGaJhZPctzhvvChIjQ2Y8oF7lvG4hH9R8hkz0LEJuj4I4vAXC0twUFFw06Dbmhxl_o115PQTbGBT_vnM0evTdAIvgp9Rvq5C3AyCAXAldWs9thIBTYq3llk48c9Q6sYNAm7oSgDnKjwxX4KByDOz5z121zeYtpBZJ9c8WzY